WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.230 --> 00:00:06.210
- So if you get a bad response

2
00:00:06.210 --> 00:00:07.920
or just one you're not happy with,

3
00:00:07.920 --> 00:00:09.150
give us a thumbs down.

4
00:00:09.150 --> 00:00:11.820
Like, it's okay. You know,
our feelings won't be hurt.

5
00:00:11.820 --> 00:00:13.350
We actually want this feedback.

6
00:00:13.350 --> 00:00:14.370
Give us a thumbs down.

7
00:00:14.370 --> 00:00:16.080
And then every once in a while,

8
00:00:16.080 --> 00:00:19.957
there'll be a feedback box
that pops up that says like,

9
00:00:19.957 --> 00:00:20.880
"What went wrong?"

10
00:00:20.880 --> 00:00:22.680
Or, "How can we make this better?"

11
00:00:22.680 --> 00:00:24.690
And there are a few select options.

12
00:00:24.690 --> 00:00:25.950
So you can just select one of those

13
00:00:25.950 --> 00:00:27.870
or you can type in what went wrong.

14
00:00:27.870 --> 00:00:30.360
And what's really helpful
there is not only saying

15
00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:31.200
what went wrong,

16
00:00:31.200 --> 00:00:32.520
but what you expected

17
00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:34.890
or what you would've wanted
the response to look like.

18
00:00:34.890 --> 00:00:38.430
And, yeah, this is data that
we analyze all the time.

19
00:00:38.430 --> 00:00:41.640
We really wanna see where the
model is struggling or failing

20
00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:44.240
and so we can just make it
better in the next round.